# Project 2 - Fake Review Detector

## What I Built

Built my first Machine Learning model capable of classifying reviews as genuine or fake using TF-IDF and Naive Bayes.

---

## Architecture

Dataset
↓
Cleaning
↓
TF-IDF
↓
Machine Learning Model
↓
Prediction

---

## Biggest Things I Learned

- ML learns patterns from data instead of explicit rules.
- TF-IDF converts text into numbers.
- Features matter more than algorithms.
- Training and testing must remain separate.

---

## Mental Models

- Machine Learning is pattern recognition.
- Features are how a model "sees" data.
- Better data usually beats a more complicated model.

